You could taste the oil, which the oil tasted as if other items were fried into as well. I couldn’t bare to eat it. I paid for it and I left.  Also, most places serve a small amount of fruit with it but for $10.00 you’ll get fried bread in old oil. The server also brought a small jar of syrup which it was sticky and the lid had fuss and dust stick on. I gave it a star because service was sympathetic. I would not recommend this place to anyone, or at least the French toast.  Try this place at your own risk.
